#  Doubly Linear Linked List in C++

This repository contains C++ programs that demonstrate the implementation of a **Doubly Linear Linked List (DLL)** using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP). The programs are designed in a step-by-step manner, starting from the basic node structure to a complete menu-driven implementation.

---

# What is a Doubly Linear Linked List?

A **Doubly Linear Linked List** is a dynamic linear data structure in which **each node stores three parts**:

- **Previous Pointer (prev)** → Points to the previous node.
- **Data** → Stores the actual information.
- **Next Pointer (next)** → Points to the next node.

Unlike a Singly Linked List, every node maintains links in **both forward and backward directions**, allowing traversal from **head to tail** as well as **tail to head**.

---

#  Node Structure

```
+--------+-----------+--------+
|  Prev  |   Data    |  Next  |
+--------+-----------+--------+
```

- **Prev** → Address of the previous node
- **Data** → Value stored in the node
- **Next** → Address of the next node

---

#  Visualization

```
NULL
  ↑
  │
+------+------+      +------+------+      +------+------+
| Prev | 11  | ---> | Prev | 21  | ---> | Prev | 51  | ---> NULL
| NULL | Next| <--- | Addr | Next| <--- | Addr | NULL|
+------+------+      +------+------+      +------+------+
```

or simply,

```
NULL <- [11] <-> [21] <-> [51] -> NULL
```

