#  Features of Doubly Linear Linked List

- Dynamic memory allocation
- Bidirectional traversal
- Efficient insertion and deletion
- No contiguous memory required
- Easy implementation of forward and backward navigation
- Suitable for applications requiring two-way traversal

---

#  Advantages

- Forward as well as backward traversal
- Faster deletion when node reference is available
- Easy insertion before or after any node
- Better flexibility than Singly Linked List

---

#  Limitations

- Requires extra memory for the previous pointer
- More pointer manipulation
- Slightly complex implementation compared to Singly Linked List

